Description: Concurrent WiFi and Hotspot Manager for Linux
 A GTK3 application that enables concurrent WiFi and hotspot mode.
 Allows users to stay connected to WiFi while broadcasting a hotspot
 to share their internet connection with other devices.
 .
 Features:
  - Concurrent Mode: WiFi connection stays active while hotspot runs
  - GTK3 GUI with system tray indicator
  - Hardware detection for concurrent mode support
  - Connected devices monitoring
  - CLI interface for scripting
  - Auto-recovery when WiFi reconnects